<p>I am developing a WPF application with SQL Server 2014.</p>  <p>In our server side, I have created SQL Login as </p>  <pre><code>CREATE LOGIN &lt;username&gt; WITH PASSWORD = &lt;oldPassword&gt; MUST_CHANGE,CHECK_EXPIRATION=ON,CHECK_POLICY=ON, DEFAULT_DATABASE =&lt;databaseName&gt; DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=[English] </code></pre>  <p>Now after changing the password of above user by</p>  <pre><code>ALTER LOGIN &lt;username&gt; WITH PASSWORD = &lt;newPassword&gt; , OLD_PASSWORD =&lt;oldPassword&gt; , DEFAULT_DATABASE=&lt;databaseName&gt;, DEFAULT_LANGUAGE=[English] </code></pre>  <p>I am able to open this connection with Old Password and new password both (by using  VS2013 C# connection string ). Condition : It will work only till we restart our server or service.</p>  <p>As per the requirement, user should be able to login only with new password. Can this community help me.</p>  <p>Do we have some restriction in SQL to open connection/login only with New Password. Thanks in Advance.</p>